01:02:48.573 --> 01:02:50.199
But I was wrong.

01:02:58.416 --> 01:03:00.501
<i>(Regan) We were always anxious,</i>
<i>of course, to get off the plane.</i>

01:03:00.543 --> 01:03:02.044
<i>That was a long flight.</i>

01:03:02.086 --> 01:03:05.672
But we got off the plane
and we put our bags on our backs

01:03:05.715 --> 01:03:11.094
and, you know, they were heavy and
we just kept moving towards the airport.

01:03:12.096 --> 01:03:15.599
And suddenly,
three, two limousines pulled up

01:03:17.685 --> 01:03:19.603
and we were sure
that they weren't for us.

01:03:19.729 --> 01:03:22.523
We were like kind of
walking around them.

01:03:22.565 --> 01:03:25.234
Like, ''Oh, we better get out
of these people's way

01:03:25.360 --> 01:03:27.694
'''cause they're important people
in limos.''

01:03:27.737 --> 01:03:30.697
But they were for us.
And that's when it began.

01:03:30.740 --> 01:03:34.743
<i>It was all another world.</i>
<i>It was another world.</i>

01:03:34.869 --> 01:03:40.082
<i>(Eva) Just like you would see people...</i>
<i>over Madonna or...</i>

01:03:40.208 --> 01:03:45.587
Like stepping out into the wind
and the paparazzi and all the...

01:03:45.630 --> 01:03:51.593
you know, the production assistants
and everybody are there to welcome him

01:03:51.719 --> 01:03:54.930
and take us into the VIP suite.

01:03:55.056 --> 01:03:59.226
<i>(Regan)</i> The white carpeting.
You know, that was something that

01:03:59.269 --> 01:04:03.814
never would we ever even dream
of walking on white carpeting,

01:04:03.940 --> 01:04:05.983
especially in your shoes. (laughs)

01:04:06.776 --> 01:04:09.444
<i>(Segerman) They put him in a limo</i>
<i>and they drove him into the city.</i>

01:04:09.487 --> 01:04:14.324
<i>And along the way, on all the lampposts,</i>
<i>were placards advertising the concert.</i>

01:04:14.409 --> 01:04:17.244
And he saw his face on every lamppost
