01:04:17.287 --> 01:04:19.830
and he'd go,
''There I am, there I am, there I am.''

01:04:19.956 --> 01:04:22.791
<i>(Eva) So we came</i>
<i>and we got to meet all the people.</i>

01:04:22.834 --> 01:04:26.587
<i>We got to meet Craig Bartholomew</i>
<i>and their family and their kids</i>

01:04:26.629 --> 01:04:28.630
<i>and Stephen Segerman.</i>

01:04:28.756 --> 01:04:32.426
And everybody was just so happy.
Everybody was thrilled.

01:04:32.468 --> 01:04:33.927
We were even happier.

01:04:34.470 --> 01:04:35.804
<i>Möller)</i> Stephen phoned me.

01:04:35.847 --> 01:04:38.181
He said, ''You will never believe this...

01:04:39.475 --> 01:04:41.602
''but Rodriguez is coming to South Africa

01:04:41.644 --> 01:04:43.437
''and we can be the opening band.

01:04:43.479 --> 01:04:47.107
''Do you wanna do it?''
I said, ''Of course we wanna do it.''

01:04:48.443 --> 01:04:51.486
''Why? Where is he?''
''Now they found him.

01:04:51.613 --> 01:04:55.115
''They found him, he's alive, he's gonna
come and tour in South Africa.''

01:04:55.158 --> 01:04:59.328
''Are we gonna be the opening band?''
So I couldn't really believe this.

01:05:00.830 --> 01:05:05.459
And then I got all the information:
he's living in Detroit and everything.

01:05:05.501 --> 01:05:07.169
And then a little while later he said,

01:05:07.211 --> 01:05:09.838
''Look, it turns out
he hasn't got a band.

01:05:09.964 --> 01:05:13.508
''Could we be the support band?''
I mean his band.

01:05:14.469 --> 01:05:18.013
I remember, even then, we were sort of,

01:05:19.515 --> 01:05:21.350
''Is this really gonna be Rodriguez?''

01:05:21.392 --> 01:05:24.019
We'll only know
if he can actually sing these songs.

01:05:24.145 --> 01:05:27.397
I mean, we don't know.
What if it's just some guy? (chuckles)

01:05:27.899 --> 01:05:29.024
<i>(Sandra) It was just like</i>

01:05:29.150 --> 01:05:30.317
<i>one day we heard about it</i>

01:05:30.360 --> 01:05:32.653
<i>and the next day we were there,</i>

01:05:34.030 --> 01:05:35.864
<i>trying to believe our eyes,</i>

01:05:35.990 --> 01:05:38.867
<i>thinking it was just all very shocking.</i>

01:05:38.993 --> 01:05:41.161
<i>I don't know, he took to it really easy.</i>

01:05:41.204 --> 01:05:43.538
<i>He just walked in and did his thing</i>

01:05:43.581 --> 01:05:47.167
<i>and I was amazed that he did so well.</i>

01:05:47.210 --> 01:05:48.210
<i>But he's not all</i>

01:05:48.336 --> 01:05:49.378
<i>''head in the clouds'' kinda guy.</i>

01:05:49.504 --> 01:05:53.215
<i>He's a little bit too much grounded.</i>

01:05:53.299 --> 01:05:54.883
<i>He didn't take advantage</i>

01:05:54.926 --> 01:05:57.052
<i>of all the amenities and stuff.</i>

01:05:57.136 --> 01:05:59.888
He didn't sleep in the big
double king size bed.

01:05:59.931 --> 01:06:03.725
He kinda curled up on the love seat
and I found him there and...

01:06:03.768 --> 01:06:07.229
Yeah, he just didn't think somebody
should have to make another bed

01:06:07.271 --> 01:06:09.231
because he messed it up or...

01:06:09.273 --> 01:06:10.649
<i>(Regan) There was a time</i>

01:06:10.733 --> 01:06:12.776
<i>where I stayed in the house we were at</i>

01:06:12.902 --> 01:06:15.404
<i>and everyone else had gone out.</i>

01:06:15.488 --> 01:06:17.114
<i>The phone rang and it kept ringing,</i>

01:06:17.240 --> 01:06:19.324
<i>so I decided to answer it.</i>

01:06:19.409 --> 01:06:20.784
And it was a reporter

01:06:20.910 --> 01:06:22.744
looking to speak with Rodriguez

01:06:22.829 --> 01:06:25.789
and set up time for an interview.

01:06:26.499 --> 01:06:31.253
And then, before she hung up,
after I told her to call back later

01:06:31.295 --> 01:06:33.672
to talk to someone
'cause I couldn't help her,

01:06:33.756 --> 01:06:38.343
she told me that she wanted to know,
between she and I,

01:06:38.428 --> 01:06:40.345
if it was the real Rodriguez.

01:06:40.430 --> 01:06:41.930
(indistinct chatter)

01:06:43.016 --> 01:06:45.267
