(inaudible over cheering)

01:13:40.433 --> 01:13:42.892
<i>(Malan) Well, isn't this all</i>
<i>our great fate?</i>

01:13:42.935 --> 01:13:47.856
Your dreams of yourself, the higher
forms of yourself is that one day

01:13:47.940 --> 01:13:52.485
you will be recognised and that
your talents and everything else,

01:13:53.446 --> 01:13:56.030
will suddenly become visible
to the world.

01:13:56.115 --> 01:14:00.618
I mean, most of us die
without coming anywhere close

01:14:00.703 --> 01:14:03.788
to that sort of magic.

01:14:03.873 --> 01:14:05.248
<i>I tried to get him to talk about that</i>

01:14:05.332 --> 01:14:06.624
<i>when I interviewed him,</i>

01:14:06.709 --> 01:14:08.126
<i>about how strange it was,</i>

01:14:08.210 --> 01:14:10.420
<i>and I got absolutely nothing back.</i>

01:14:10.504 --> 01:14:12.088
<i>Absolutely nothing back.</i>

01:14:12.173 --> 01:14:13.381
<i>And I couldn't tell whether</i>

01:14:13.466 --> 01:14:15.633
<i>he was just like sort of cripplingly shy</i>

01:14:15.718 --> 01:14:16.843
<i>or whether I was</i>

01:14:16.927 --> 01:14:18.052
<i>asking the wrong questions</i>

01:14:18.137 --> 01:14:19.179
<i>or there was a language barrier</i>

01:14:19.263 --> 01:14:20.472
<i>or whatever. He just...</i>

01:14:20.598 --> 01:14:25.602
Maybe that was OK as well
because he preserved his mystery.

01:14:25.686 --> 01:14:27.729
I walked away
from that interview saying,

01:14:28.022 --> 01:14:30.690
''This is all too strange to be true.''

01:14:30.774 --> 01:14:33.401
<i>It remains too strange to be true.</i>

01:14:33.486 --> 01:14:34.736
<i>''These are the days</i>

01:14:34.820 --> 01:14:36.362
<i>''of miracles and wonder.''</i>

01:14:36.447 --> 01:14:37.989
(loud cheering)

